  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 160°C. Roughly chop the tomatoes into chunky wedges and\nadd to a large bowl. Sprinkle with salt and toss and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drizzle the chicken with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Heat a large non-stick pan over a high heat. Add the chicken thighs to the pan and cook for 10-15 mins, until cooked through, set aside to cool."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tear the croissants into large chunks and add to a baking sheet. Season with salt\nand pepper then then slide into the oven for 10 mins – until golden and crisp-\nyou don’t need any oil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Make the dressing by whisking the ingredients with 3 tbsp olive oil. Season with\nsalt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the tomatoes, then tip back into the bowl. Slice the chicken and add to\nthe bowl along with most of the basil leaves. Use a peeler to peel most of the\nParmesan into the bowl. Add half the dressing and then tip onto a platter.\nSnuggle the croissant croutons into the salad. Drizzle the remaining dressing,\nthen finish with a pinch of chilli flakes, reserved basil leaves, Parmesan shavings\nand a crack of black pepper."
    }
